Use `%nrstr` to mask the macro invocation character (`%`).  This can be placed inside double-quotes to allow the string macro variable to be resolved. The second `%` for the trailing any match does not need to be masked because it&#39;s following character is `&quot;` which would not trigger attempt to invoke a macro.

    %let string = an;
    
    proc sql;
      create table an_students as
      select * from sashelp.class
